dCmd_Inst.dCmd:
UPDATE control_load_history
SET status = 'FAILED', 
finish_timestamp = $$CurrentTimeStamp,
updated_at = $$CurrentTimeStamp
WHERE data_flow_name = 'DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner' AND status= 'RUNNING';

UPDATE control_load_history
SET status = 'SUCCEEDED', 
finish_timestamp = $$CurrentTimeStamp,
SRC_source_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.SRC_dim_person.SourceCount  , 
SRC_process_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.SRC_dim_person.ProcessCount  , 
SRC_target_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.SRC_dim_person.TargetCount  , 
SRC_bad_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.SRC_dim_person.BadCount  ,
TGT_source_count =   $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.TGT_fact_geo_location_person_partner.SourceCount  , 
TGT_process_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.TGT_fact_geo_location_person_partner.ProcessCount  , 
TGT_target_count  =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.TGT_fact_geo_location_person_partner.TargetCount   , 
TGT_bad_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner.TGT_fact_geo_location_person_partner.BadCount   ,
updated_at = $$CurrentTimeStamp
WHERE data_flow_name = 'DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner' AND status= 'RUNNING'

INSERT INTO control_load_history (data_flow_name, status, start_timestamp, created_at)
VALUES ('DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner', 'RUNNING', $$CurrentTimeStamp, $$CurrentTimeStamp);

UPDATE control_load_history
SET status = 'ABORTED', 
finish_timestamp = $$CurrentTimeStamp,
updated_at = $$CurrentTimeStamp
WHERE data_flow_name ='DF_LOAD_fact_geo_location_person_partner' AND status= 'RUNNING';
